The things you refer to ("executing sacred Dharma/Karma", "blessed person", "love of Humanity", "selfeless service", "Kundalini awakening", "Mantra Siddhi", "Divine Grace" etc) are all good things, but they are not enough to make one a rishi, i.e. one who swiftly flows with divine will with zero resistance.
 
